Based on your query, the section you are looking for is the initial set of assumptions that frame the entire prospectus. This is typically found at the very beginning of the document, following the cover page and table of contents.

Here is the retrieved section that outlines the capitalization assumptions:

**[SECTION: PREAMBLE]**
Unless otherwise indicated, all information contained in this prospectus assumes or gives effect to:

*   prior to the completion of this offering, pursuant to the terms of our certificate of formation in effect as a private company prior to this offering, the reclassification of all of the outstanding shares of our Class C common stock into an aggregate of [number] shares of Class A common stock (the “Class C Reclassification”) and the conversion of the outstanding shares of all our preferred stock into an aggregate of [number] shares of our Class A common stock and [number] shares of our Class B common stock (the “Preferred Conversion”) ;
*   the effectiveness of our charter and bylaws, which will become effective upon the completion of this offering;
*   an initial public offering price of $[amount] per share of Class A common stock (the midpoint of the price range set forth on the cover of this prospectus);
*   that the underwriters do not exercise their option to purchase additional shares of Class A common stock from us; and
*   no purchase of shares of Class A common stock in this offering by our directors, officers or existing shareholders.

This foundational block establishes the hypothetical post-offering capital structure upon which all presented financial data, share counts, and per-share calculations are based. It specifically addresses your points regarding the reclassification of Class C shares, the conversion of all preferred stock, and the standard IPO condition of using the offering price midpoint.
